"Jessie" (sp?)

Master of Interior Architecture and Product Design
Kansas State University

Originally from Andover, Kansas, Jessica’s hobbies are throwing ceramics on the pottery wheel and practicing yoga. She’s passionate about little adventures, and wants to ride in a hot air balloon. While earning her master’s degree, she designed and built furniture in the program’s workshop. Jessica’s favorite project at studioSIX5 was sketching and designing the custom furniture for the Eden Hill Continuing Care Retirement Community in New Braunfels, Texas. Her blonde cocker spaniel is named Tula.

studioSIX5
September 2014 –

Bachelor of Science in Interior Design
The University of Texas at Austin

NCIDQ (National Council for Interior Design Qualification)

Rayann began life in Indianapolis, but got to Austin as soon as she could. She has 20+ years experience as an interior designer. She also spent more than three years working for a large international construction company on the U.S. Embassy project in Berlin. Beyond that, she’s worked for firms in Tucson, Arizona, Paris, Texas, Waco, Texas, and Austin.

With this varied experience and an apparent lust for adventure, she has moved across two oceans, and loves to travel, quilt and play golf. She is passionate about her family, and particularly partial to ice cream and margaritas. Rayann’s favorite projects are Sun City in Georgetown and Providence Park in Waco. Her favorite books are Pillars of the Earth and Kite Runner; her favorite movie is Gone with the Wind. Musically, you’d find everything from Andrea Boccelli to Alan Jackson to Lady Gaga to Pink on her iPod.

If she weren’t a designer, she believes she’d be doing forensic science. She prides herself on being a self starter, and says she has a high attention to detail with the ability to turn a vision into results.

Bachelor of Arts—Interior Design, California State University, Fresno

National Council for Interior Design Qualification (NCIDQ) #24326

A native of Fresno, California, Stephanie made the move to Austin to join studioSIX5. She has 10 years’ experience in interior design and project management. She believes the most important part of being an interior designer is maintaining constant contact and open communication with the client. Her favorite studioSIX5 projects are Cottonwood Place in Holladay, Utah, The Village at Stonebridge in McKinney, Texas, Eden Hill in New Braunfels, Texas, and Vivante on the Coast in Costa Mesa, California.

Stephanie is passionate about cooking, family and traveling. Her hobby is doing anything outdoors with her family. She loves country music and music from the 80s and 90s, and is a reality TV junkie. She drove to Austin from Fresno in a car with three dogs, one cat and two kids. Sweets are her guilty pleasure.

National Council for Interior Design Qualifications: certificate holder #020474

Certified Aging-in-Place Specialist

Ron is originally from Alma, Arkansas. Prior to returning to professional practice; Ron was program coordinator for interior design in the School of Family and Consumer Sciences at Texas State University, San Marcos. Ron has taught interior design at the University of Arkansas, Colorado State University, El Centro College (program coordinator), and the University of North Texas (program coordinator). He is the author of three books and numerous articles, including Finding a Place Called Home: The Resident’s Journey in Assisted Living. He is passionate about modern furniture, art, teaching, writing, nature, animals, and, of course, designs for senior living. His hobbies are painting and ice skating–in fact, he was a figure skater in his youth, and says if he weren’t a designer, he’d be a figure skating coach. His favorite books are his own: Color + Design and Color Studies 3rd Edition. He was in marching band for 12 years, including four years in the University of Arkansas Razorback Marching Band, and marched in Bill Clinton’s inaugural presidential parade in Washington. He is devoted to his dog, Dixon.

As Design Director, Claire implements a proven track record of providing personal service through an integrated team approach -- creating a Design Studio that offers a hands-on, full scope approach fostering long standing client relationships and an excellent reputation for achieving perfection in her jobs.

Claire's extensive design background was embarked at UC Davis where she studied Environmental Design with an emphasis in Interior Architecture. Eager to learn more, she furthered her studies to the east coast and abroad -- New York, Denmark, and Spain. She graduated top of her class from Pratt Institute in Brooklyn, New York receiving her Masters in Interior Design.

Through her intensive studies and experience, she has gained a broad understanding of design principles and practice. In her time at Western, she has demonstrated creative and challenging approaches to design, incorporating technical drawing and computer skills with the history and theory of interior design, the principles of color and lighting, a deep understanding of human factors and the importance of sustainability in built environments.
